And, through this spiritual dying, his (a man’s) soul is taken from
him, and lifted up on high： while his body is still upon earth, his
spirit and heart are already in his eternal Fatherland; and all his
actions have a heavenly source, and seem no longer to belong to this
earth. For he lives no longer according to the flesh, but according to
the Spirit, not in the unfruitful works of darkness, but in the light
and in the day—in works that stand the test of fire.
